# .node-version — pins the Node.js version for this repository.
#
# WHAT THIS FILE IS FOR
#   This is the companion to .nvmrc for version managers that read
#   `.node-version` instead of (or in addition to) `.nvmrc` — for example
#   nodenv, asdf (asdf-nodejs), fnm, and Volta. Keeping both files lets every
#   contributor land on the same Node runtime regardless of which manager they
#   use. The version below MUST stay identical to the one in .nvmrc.
#
# WHEN TO CHANGE THE VERSION
#   - Only when the project intentionally adopts a new Node release (a
#     dependency requires it, or to pick up an LTS/security update).
#   - Update this file AND .nvmrc together, then keep both in sync with CI
#     (actions/setup-node `node-version`) and the `engines.node` range in
#     package.json, so local, CI, and editor all agree.
#   - After switching, reinstall dependencies in the new runtime:
#         npm ci
#
# NOTE: nvm, fnm, and Volta strip these comment lines. Some readers (notably
# older nodenv/asdf) expect a bare version with no comments — if your manager
# fails to parse this file, reduce it to just the single version line below.
22.22.3
